LEO PRIME gives STRAIGHT SHOT an &#39;are you insane&#39; look as he turned to
face her. &quot;How would you propose to and &#39;save&#39; Waspinator?&quot; He asked,
clearly agaisnt such an idea. &quot;He has been a Predacon for quite a
little while now. I believe he was a henchman of Megatrons before he
even came to the Earth.&quot;

Turning to look at the screen, &quot;We can&#39;t have the remaining teams
trying to break into the predacon headquarters trying to rescue a
Predacon who has already made his choice.&quot; He looked back at STRAIGHT
SHOT, &quot;And how could you ever know that it is not a trick designed to
subtract more from our forces.&quot;

He shook his head, &quot;No, we cannot be trying to save Waspinator right
now, not with so many other people at stake.&quot; LEO turned to look back
at the screen, &quot;Like Tuscon, or Rodimus, or Polar Claw and his team.&quot;
LEO fell silent for a moment, but STRAIGHT SHOT probrably knew that
POLAR CLAW&#39;s team also included NIGHTSHIFT.

LEO PRIME sighed.

&quot;You do realize what you are going to have to do.&quot; LORD ELDER said as
he came to stand next to LEO.

There was a nod from LEO as he looked back up at the viewscreen.
&quot;Yes.&quot; He stabbed a finger down on the control panel in front of him.
&quot;Wingcaliber and Santon, report the main docking bay.&quot; He said.

He looked at LORD ELDER, &quot;You and Legacy will need to remain here
along with the fuzors and Bump.&quot; He shook his head, &quot;Tuscon has
started something with the Predacons, and now it may be that we will
need their help to see this through.&quot;

